{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"29d7344f-ddf4-4310-8853-60334d11b06d","content":"The standard approach is to **abstract the file system behind an interface** and inject it:\n\n1. **Use `System.IO.Abstractions`** (NuGet package) — it provides `IFileSystem` with `IFile`, `IDirectory`, etc. that mirror the static `System.IO` APIs. No need to roll your own.\n\n2. **Inject `IFileSystem`** into classes that do I/O:\n   ```csharp\n   public class MyService(IFileSystem fs)\n   {\n       public void Save(string path, string data) => fs.File.WriteAllText(path, data);\n       public string Load(string path) => fs.File.ReadAllText(path);\n       public bool HasDir(string path) => fs.Directory.Exists(path);\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **In tests**, use `MockFileSystem` (ships with the package):\n   ```csharp\n   var fs = new MockFileSystem();\n   fs.AddDirectory(\"/data\");\n   var svc = new MyService(fs);\n   svc.Save(\"/data/file.txt\", \"hello\");\n   Assert.Equal(\"hello\", svc.Load(\"/data/file.txt\"));\n   ```\n\n4. **In production DI**:\n   ```csharp\n   services.AddSingleton<IFileSystem, FileSystem>();\n   ```\n\nThis gives you full in-memory test coverage with zero disk I/O, and the refactor is mostly mechanical — replace `File.` with `_fs.File.` and `Directory.` with `_fs.Directory.`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"db2e12f6-08e8-4b85-9bf6-e10779dbc0ca","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about making file system operations testable in their .NET/C# project. They have `File.WriteAllText`, `File.ReadAllText`, and `Directory.Exists` calls scattered across their code.\n\nThis is a general software engineering question, not a task requiring code changes. I should give concise advice.\n\nThe standard approach is to introduce an abstraction (interface) over the file system operations, then use dependency injection. There's also `System.IO.Abstractions` — a well-known NuGet package that provides this exact thing.\n\nLet me give a concise answer.","outputTokens":516,"requestId":"0BC3:3A1531:5387D4:611228:69F013AD"},"id":"ab2ba2f3-a1ed-4ef7-ac9c-11615246ad5b","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:56:08.781Z","parentId":"2708f6cd-81cb-40a0-a605-26b07444077d"}
